# Module pattern

- Logic lives in `service.ts`
- Types in `types.ts`
- Shared shapes in `contracts.ts`
- Read the module `README.md` before editing

# Boundaries

- Exam Engine owns exam timing and exam mode rules
- Saved Progress owns persistence and resume storage requests
- Power Grid aggregates activity into next steps
- Content and CMS stay separate from student progress logic
- Access Arrangements stay framework-neutral and separate

# Before changing a module

1. Read `src/modules/<name>/README.md`
2. Check existing `service.ts`, `types.ts`, and `contracts.ts`
3. Match naming and patterns already in that module
